"{\"uid\": \"independent.co.uk-sport-olympics-swimming-adam-peaty-olympics-paris-2024-underdog-b2564569.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Notifications can be managed in browser preferences.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 52, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in  Swipe for next article  Interview:After more than half a decade as a swimming god, Peaty has been proven to be painfully mortal in in recent times but believes that makes him stronger than ever as he heads to Paris seeking Olympic history  Removed from bookmarks  I would like to be emailed about offers, events and updates from The Independent.\", \"from\": 54, \"to\": 537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 401, \"end\": 406, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999489127744, \"rank\": 5.108700315601397e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read ourPrivacy notice  The legendary American football coach Vince Lombardi famously said: \\\"Show me a good loser and I will show you a loser\\\".\", \"from\": 538, \"to\": 681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 600, \"end\": 614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vince_Lombardi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Vince Lombardi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vince_Lombardi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vince_Lombardi\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"What is often omitted is the second half of that quote, which changes the meaning entirely: \\\"But show me a gracious loser and I will show you someone who will always be a winner\\\".\", \"from\": 682, \"to\": 861, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It is the latter implication thatAdam Peaty, Britain'sgreatest-ever swimmer,is applying to his own sporting ambitions.\", \"from\": 863, \"to\": 981, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The world record holder and three-timeOlympicchampion spent more thanhalf a decade as a god,even amongswimming's elite.\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 1102, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But after becoming the first British swimmer ever to retain anOlympictitle - doing so inthe 100m breaststroke in Tokyo- Peaty's invincibility has been brokenover the last three years.\", \"from\": 1103, \"to\": 1286, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1132, \"end\": 1139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9852538873391455, \"rank\": 0.00834753301907184, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}, {\"begin\": 1216, \"end\": 1221, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9997267003629755, \"rank\": 0.00027337412594620827, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He suffered a first loss in his specialist event in eight yearsat the 2022 Commonwealth Games, and a combination of injury and abreak for mental health reasons,mean that he has missed three successive World Championships.\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1509, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"His world record remains a distance clear of the field, but Peaty headsto Paris for his third Olympicsin an unfamiliar position.\", \"from\": 1511, \"to\": 1639, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1585, \"end\": 1590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999489127744, \"rank\": 5.108700315601397e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He might not quite be the underdog he claims, but he is no longer the overwhelming favourite.\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And the ultimate winner is happy with that position, having learned how to cope with defeat.\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1827, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He said: \\\"Going into these Games, especially the last 12 months, I have enjoyed being the person with the bow and arrow and not the person being fired at.\", \"from\": 1829, \"to\": 1983, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It gives you a different approach to it.\", \"from\": 1984, \"to\": 2024, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is no real pressure on me.\", \"from\": 2025, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Yes, I am Olympic champion and people are going for that crown but anyone that follows the sport, will know I have not really raced, I have not really won anything since 2022 or 2021 but I am ok with that.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2265, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am the underdog and I enjoy being the underdog, fighting my way through the ranks.\", \"from\": 2267, \"to\": 2352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If anything, it's shown me how to lose with grace.\", \"from\": 2353, \"to\": 2403, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Before, I used to lose and I would tear everything up, I did not like it.\", \"from\": 2404, \"to\": 2477, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have been like that since I was a kid.\", \"from\": 2478, \"to\": 2518, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Now, at 29 years old, I have learned how to lose.\", \"from\": 2520, \"to\": 2570, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It does suck because I know how much I invest in myself and train and how much Team GB and Aquatics GB put in.\", \"from\": 2571, \"to\": 2681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2657, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"score\": 0.9999999997221494, \"rank\": 2.7490139223135945e-10, \"text\": \"Team GB\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Team_GB\"}, {\"begin\": 2671, \"end\": 2673, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9213943397765029, \"rank\": 0.08524585981340387, \"text\": \"GB\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We do not lose the ferocity, but you must bear in mind that you must lose sometimes to get these wins.\\\"\", \"from\": 2682, \"to\": 2785, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Peaty is one of over 1,000 elite athletes on UK Sport's National Lottery-funded World Class Programme, allowing them to train full time, have access to the world's best coaches and benefit from pioneering medical support - this is vital for his pathway to theParis 2024Games  Peaty heads to Paris looking to match Michael Phelps and become only the second man to win gold in the same swimming event at three successive Olympics.\", \"from\": 2787, \"to\": 3215, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2832, \"end\": 2840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 2832, \"end\": 2840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"UK Sport\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/UK_Sport\"}, {\"begin\": 3078, \"end\": 3083, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999489127744, \"rank\": 5.108700315601397e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 3101, \"end\": 3115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.483246855339012e-36, \"text\": \"Michael Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Phelps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And after three years in which he experienced some of his lowest ebbs, struggling with depression and alcohol problems, Peaty is at peace with himself.\", \"from\": 3217, \"to\": 3368, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He explained: \\\"When you achieve what I have in the sport, Olympic golds, world records, that comes at a cost.\", \"from\": 3370, \"to\": 3479, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We all know that sport is extremely demanding.\", \"from\": 3480, \"to\": 3526, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are continually learning as athletes and as people.\", \"from\": 3528, \"to\": 3583, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport is very relatable to life because it is so, so tough.\", \"from\": 3584, \"to\": 3643, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You have those tough moments in your life where you must overcome them.\", \"from\": 3644, \"to\": 3715, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the same in sport.\", \"from\": 3716, \"to\": 3739, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I would not say it's a new me.\", \"from\": 3740, \"to\": 3770, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"There is still the deep chimp inside me who gets the job done, with a lot of anger.\", \"from\": 3771, \"to\": 3854, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But there is also a new side of me which can process things a little bit more easily and consistently.\", \"from\": 3855, \"to\": 3957, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I have had a lot of help from various people to help me get to that place.\", \"from\": 3958, \"to\": 4032, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This person now is going to carry on for the rest of my life.\", \"from\": 4034, \"to\": 4096, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The one I had in Tokyo and Rio is not sustainable for the rest of your life because you cannot have that approach for everything.\", \"from\": 4097, \"to\": 4226, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4114, \"end\": 4119, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9997267003629755, \"rank\": 0.00027337412594620827, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 4124, \"end\": 4127, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9996929528524229, \"rank\": 0.0003071414543151554, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2016_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I am more relaxed in my approach now, I am a bit more knowledgeable of self and I guess when I look at myself in the mirror, I am very peaceful.\", \"from\": 4228, \"to\": 4373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As soon as you stop running from yourself, that is when you start living your true life.\", \"from\": 4374, \"to\": 4462, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In sport that is when you are most dangerous to everyone else.\", \"from\": 4463, \"to\": 4525, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am not afraid to lose, I am not afraid to win.\", \"from\": 4526, \"to\": 4574, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"How can you beat an athlete like that?\", \"from\": 4575, \"to\": 4613, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I can not control what anyone else does but I can stand behind the blocks and give it my best.\\\"\", \"from\": 4614, \"to\": 4709, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The more sustainable Peaty is ready to accept that if his best is not enough this time, he will be able to lose with grace.\", \"from\": 4711, \"to\": 4834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Knowing Peaty, we might not find out.\", \"from\": 4835, \"to\": 4872, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"National Lottery players raise more than \\u00a330million a week for good causes including vital funding into sport - from grassroots to elite.\", \"from\": 4874, \"to\": 5011, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4874, \"end\": 4890, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"score\": 0.9999999897149792, \"rank\": 1.0284872744888355e-08, \"text\": \"National Lottery\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/National_Lottery_Heritage_Fund\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"To find out more visit:www.lotterygoodcauses.org.uk#TNLAthletes  Join thought-provoking conversations, follow other Independent readers and see their replies  Please refresh the page or navigate to another page on the site to be automatically logged inPlease refresh your browser to be logged in\", \"from\": 5012, \"to\": 5307, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5128, \"end\": 5139, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3351084401284382e-17, \"text\": \"Independent\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/The_Independent\"}]}]}"